Dialogs.Dialog: That's why I'm worried about the book recommended by the library committee. What should I do...
There's a book I've been wanting to read...
Yes, why don't you read "Red-haired Anne"？
"Red-haired Anne", is that a TV show or a movie？
Yes. It's often on display. A red-haired girl from an orphanage--
Yes, I know... It seems that it's for elementary and junior high school girls...
Umm, I'm not sure. Even if it's "meaningful to read", I'm not that convinced...
Yes... after all, I will read "Red-haired Anne".
Huh？ Have you never read it？
In the summer of my 5th grade, Mama highly recommended it to me, so I read it...
I wasn't really sure when I was asked what I thought, and Mama seemed disappointed so I said "It's funny"--
I think she knew I was lying, so I said "I'm sorry, I'll read the book".
That's right. When I heard the theme of the recommended books, I remembered it.
Perhaps now, I can read it after all this time.
Alright！ Then I will do my book review about that book too！
Emm？ Is that okay？ That book is a bit girlish...
I you think it's weird after reading it, then read another one.
If you mother recommend it that much, then will it might become your favorite ▲高嶺＊＊▲？ I want to read it too.
Yes, thank you. Then, do you want to read it together？
I've been waiting. Do you know a place where we can read it？
Then, why don't we go read？
Of course, I was waiting because I want to read it quickly.
Huh, did you forget？ It's "Red-haired Anne"！
I remember. Geez... It's about time, right？ Let's read it quickly.
That's right... Oh no, I have to read it quickly.
That's right, I have to read "Red-haired Anne"！
I wonder if ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is available？ I should call her...
Can we read together？ You know "Red-haired Anne".
Right now？ Uh... Yes. Can you come to my house？
Yes. I'll brew tea while I wait. Be careful, okay？
That's right, I wonder if that book has a sequel！
If you'd like, why we don't continue reading together？
Of course, I was thinking of inviting you. I want to continue reading.
That's nice！ Can I come over？
Go ahead. I'll wait for you with English style tea and muffins. Hehe.
I'll go right away！ I want to continue reading with you...
Do you want to continue reading the book？
If I do my best, I'll finish it in time...
Then, come here, okay？ Let's do our best, okay？
You know, I just about it...
When you read the book, why don't we do it together？ If possible, match our pace.
That way, we can discuss what we read and our thoughts of the day... Right？
I see... Do you want to try it？
I'm glad, shall we do it now？ Then, start！
▲高嶺＊＊▲, how far did you read？
Matthew picks up Anne and the two arrive at Grin Gables in a carriage.
Anne is cute, and her imagination is amazing. I hope this doesn't turns sad...
Marilla is about to take Anne out to White Sands. Trying to return Anne...
I feel sorry, like if I was there... But Cordelia-san, she has such a nice name！
Anne talks to Marilla, and eventually she can live in Grin Gables！
I was truly glad... When she says "I think you must have wanted me to do this", I burst unto tears.
Anne's original prayer before going to bed, the hearing the rumors of Diana. I couldn't stop imagining.
I want to see Diana soon, but I also want to see Ketti Morris and Violetta.
When Linde told her about her hair, Anne exploded and apologized.
Linde became a fan of Anne... It's funny. But I think red hair is nice.
Anne wears a flower- decorated hat, goes to church, and finally meets the long awaited Diana.
"I'm a friend's confidant" ...It was nice. And Diana is so cute.
She went on a picnic, and her brooch disappeared... And she found it was a misunderstanding.
It's weird Anne doesn't forgive her, and just says "Think about ice cream！", I thought it was weird...
She hit Gilbert's head with a stone plate, but Diana got drunk and she couldn't met him...
I loved school and Diana so much... And I'm somewhat happy that Marilla gets angry with her.
Anne is back in school, and she gives first aid to Minnie May's laryngitis, and Barley finally meets Diana.
I think it's amazing I can calmly cope with the acute laryngitis of a small kid... But "Anne or Cordelia".
At the night of the debate club, she jumped over Diana and aunt Josephine, and was sent to a haunted forest.
Anyway, the girls were really disciplined... I think I can't stand it...
Anne gives Alan a painful cake. And a new female Sensei is coming.
Anne says to Marilla, "Think about how to please others, not just yourself", right？ Huh, Mama often tells me that.
Anne falls down of roof in a showdown with Josie. Yes, it was a program for the Christmas program.
Looking at Anne falling, there's a point where Marilla notices, right？ Like a mother. I was in tears...
Thanks to Matthew, Anne got her puff clothes, made a it big at the concert and created a club.
Matthew shopping is so cute... I think I laughed for a while...
Anne's hair turns green. And she's made a Shirayuri's maiden... Avonley told her romance was forbidden.
Hah... I wonder when Anne will forgive Gilbert. Oh, I said it like Diana.
She spent time at Diana and Miss Burley's mansion, and Stacy invited her to enter the School's Queen class.
When she returns, Anne tells Marilla "the best thing is to come home", right？ I want to say things like that.
Anne and Diana spent their last summer vacation, and Anne passed the Queen of the School class！
I'm proud of Anne, but I understand Marilla as she's grown lonelier... Just like a real parent.
Anne does a recitation of poetry at the hotel concert... And finally leaves Grin Gables.
I wondered if I would leave home that way, and cried. I cried page after page. It's weird.
Anne returns to Grin Gables for Christmas and decided to get an Avery Scholarship.
Matthew wants more that twelve boys, right？ The day Anne returned, I started to cry... I want him to get better.
That's all for today. Don't worry, we'll continue slowly next time, okay？
Yes, just finished reading. Hah... My heart is full.
I see... Okay, I'll also take a break！
In which part are you？ Did you finish it？
How is that？ Did you progress little？
There's some left. Let's start with...
It's midpoint. I wonder how much is left...
It's almost over. The best is here...
Then, I'm a little ahead？ I should go slowly...
That so... Then, I should go slowly...
Yes. I understand. I'll go slowly...
I'm a little ahead. Work hard.
Well, I'm going ahead. It's good to do it at you pace, right？
Yes. We're about the same. Do we have the same pace？
Oh, we're about the same. I'm glad. Hehe...
Yes, almost together. Let's match out pace, right？
I'm going at the same pace. We're doing doubles？ Hehe！
Emm, that much？ I have to hurry...
I see... Then, I should hurry.
That much？ Oh, I'm getting behind...
Geez... Didn't you say we were at the same pace？
How far are you in the book？
Okay, let's round it for today！
Round it... Eh, is it over？
Okay, let's round it for today！
Yes... Well, that's a good part.
Okay, let's round it for today！
Yes... That's right, it might be just right.
Hah. It was interesting. Hey, why don't we leave it for today？
Hah... I'm satisfied. Hey, why don't we leave it for today？
Hey hey, what chapter are you reading you today？
Then, I think I'm going ahead of you.
Sorry, I seem to have gone ahead.
Well, I've gone first. I thought I adjusted my pace.
We're about the same. Yes, we go at the same pace.
Me too. We're synchronized, right？ Hehe.
I'm the same. Hooray, we did it as doubles, right？ Hehe.
That so... Am I reading too slow？
Sorry, maybe I was doing it too slow...
Geez... It's no good to read so quickly, okay？ Let's keep the same pace, right？
Hah... I have finished reading. My heart is full...
Hah... I have finished reading. I'm still at Grin Gables.
God is in heaven, and there's nothing in this world... Hah... I have finished reading.
Emm, Anne turns to Marilla and--. No, I shouldn't say it, it seems reading won't be as fun.
Hah... I'm getting more and more drawn... I wonder why did I think it was boring when I was little.
It was funny. Ahem... No, I shouldn't laugh at it.
Hah. It was interesting. If there was a child like Anne, I would be a "confidant friend"...
Hah, it was fun. Marilla and Matthew are so cute...
Hah... it's almost over. Now I'm sad after reading this book.
Would you rename Anne with whatever nice name you like？
Yes, did you gave her another name？
Right！ Besides, you call her Ann without an e, right？ So, I worried and looked at the title of the imprint...
Did you get interested？ Seeing that made me happy. It was as famous as Anne without "e".
Don't you mind？ If it doesn't have an "e", won't you feel sorry？
That-- No, you have to see it for yourself, right？ Hehe！
You know the story about the picture of Christ with children？
Yes, the one about the child who cannot enter the circle？
Yes... I could understand the feeling of that girl.
Right now, ▲高嶺＊＊▲, is one of the child in the ring？
Emm！？ No way, did you met Christ！？
Me？ Not really... No, it's nothing.
Right now you are one of the child in the ring, right ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I remembered the first time when Diana and Anne were playing for the first time. I like that.
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you play with your friends in the garden？
Only if you're a "Confidant Friend", right？
▲高嶺＊＊▲, you played with your friends in the garden, right？
Yes, but my garden isn't that big. A dryad fountain would be nice.
Only if you're a "Confidant Friend", right？
Hehe, will you play house with me in the garden？
That so！ We're going to have fun playing dolls with friends. It was fun.
Do you remember Gilbert’s "carrot", pulling on Anne's hair？
I was done the same once. But unlike Anne, I just cried all the time.
I wonder why boys do that. Don't they know it hurts？
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you get bullied like that？
Is that because he likes you？
But it's fun for girls to cry！
Then, you're still in elementary school, right？ Geez！
▲高嶺＊＊▲, did you get bullied like that？
I wore glasses when I was little-- no, I won't tell you.
Is it because the person likes you？
I often say that, but the one who did it is really disappointing. Reflect on behalf of all men.
Huh？ Did you remembered something funny？
Yes！ Matthew is so cute that I just remembered him.
When it comes to Anne and Marilla, who I'm against？
Besides, it's actually masculine, isn't it？
Ah, I love that！ Hey, can we do it again？ Right？
When it comes to Anne, you go against Marilla, right？
That's right！ I'll always be sweet to Anne. I won't look like a bad father.
That's right！ When Minnie May gets a fever, you silently prepare a carriage, right？ I think that's nice.
Hey, there was a place where Anne falls from the roof and is seriously injured, right？
There was. Was that a command game？
Yes. Marilla rushes to see Anne and is upset. I was really sad.
Tears in the eyes of the demon...
You'll realize that Anne is irreplaceable.
Yes... I think I found out why Mama wanted me to read this book.
Or tears in the eyes of the demon...
Ah, that's terrible... But when I read it before, I thought that Marilla was mean and scary.
Anne is pretty fearless, isn't she？
Fear, huh... I'm sure we've made Mama think that many times.
Do you think Anne will ever forgive Gilbert？
I don't think so, even in the story they don't say.
Is that right？ But... Isn't Anne just like Gilbert？ He's such a nice boy.
Is that what you mean by love？
It's obvious, you like Anne, right？
You think so？ Then maybe, Anne and Gilbert are...
Is that so？ I don't think that's-- Maybe, are you jealous？ Hehe！
Puh！ I'm sorry！ But, is that right？
It makes sense to study hard... There are times you are used to it, right？ I'm sure Anne feel it too, right？
Since I was born, I have never felt like that.
Your grades will improve, so do your best okay？
Are you the victim of stuffed education？
I have never felt like that since I was born.
I see... Okay. Well then, why don't we study together？
Yes. Your grades will improve, so keep doing your best, right？
That's right！ Even if it's tough, I think everyone needs something like that.
I wonder... but, aren't you excited just to learn or remember something new？
Another sigh？ Somehow, you're doing it a lot recently, don't you ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes... I was near the end of the book, and my tears were going to fall... I wonder what's wrong with me？
It's nice that you liked that book so much.
Hey, were you not moved？ That was a tearful scene, right？
A scene in which Matthew says "I would prefer 12 boys", I think that makes me sadder.
Me too！ I was in tears... Anne was so happy.
The scene where Anne says "I'm very happy I came to Grin Gables".
Me too！ I remembered when poor Anne arrived to Grin Gables...
Yes... Each person has their own way of enjoying it, right？
Huh？ Are your eyes red？ Hehe, shall we go？ Like Anne and Gilbert...
"Red-haired Anne"... And then？ Did it become your favorite ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Of course... It's really strange. It's completely different from what I read when I was a kid.
When I was a kid, I wondered what a nasty person Marilla was--
Anne couldn't have thought that much if she wasn't nice.
But, as I read now, I found myself reflected in Anne when I was a little child--
A lot of feelings that overlap with mine are now written, and--
You can see how wonderful Marilla was, even if she was mean, and even Matthew who was an old man loved Anne.
I think I understand the meaning behind Mama wanting me to read this book.
I feel like I can write a recommendation sentence with that！ Is that okay, for reference？
Let's see... Yes. Can you write it？
"Red-haired Anne"... And then？ Did it become your favorite ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes. It's the best book I've read so far.
That's amazing... What did you like？
Umm... it's hard, but for example...
Everyone- I love not only Anne and Marilla, but also Linde and Joey Pie, and I feel like I know them--
It feels like Grin Gables is a familiar place.
Right？ I think it's because the happiness and sadness of people are carefully written.
I'm sure Mama wanted to show me her favorite Grin Gables early, but...
I was a kid back then, so I'm sure I didn't have the ability to read well, and made me feel bored.
I know this since I'm older―― Huh？
I feel like I can write a recommendation sentence with this！
Really？ Then, shall we write it now？
"Red-haired Anne"... And then？ Did it become your favorite ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes. I think it's the best book I've read so far.
I'm glad about that. But... Do you feel okay？
I guess... Yes. I was so sad since I finished reading it...
Are there any sequels？ Do you want to read them？
Maybe it's because I'm getting older like in the books... I feel I have to leave my childhood with Anne.
No matter how much I like it, I think since I have the same age as Anne, will no longer read the story.
I feel like I understand. Maybe that's the reason your mother wanted you to read it, ▲高嶺＊＊▲...
I see... before I was older than Anne...
(Huh？ Looks like I can write something with this...)
Oh, Red-haired Anne... It's a good book, isn't it？
Yes. Then will you read it, sensei？
Of course. Taste changes depending on your age... Probably is a masterpiece.
And if I have a daughter in the future, I'd love her to read it...
Well, I have to make arrangements... Anyway, thank you！ I will read the book recommendation.
Ha！ It feels like I've done it！ I'm glad for you Red-haired Anne. Thank you ▲高嶺＊＊▲'s mom.
Yes. I have to tell Mama. This time I can truly say it was interesting.
Wouldn't it be nice if everyone checked the recommendation and read the book？
Maybe. However, boys may be reluctant...
It's okay. I wrote that book recommendation. I think I can persuade them.
I think that there are many people who, regardless of gender, will love to read it, like me.
Ah！ Then, is it possible to add your favorite reading for it？
(Boys who will be interested in this, don't increase！)
Oh, Red-haired Anne... it's a good book, right？
Hmm？ Taste changes depending on your age... Do you think it's a masterpiece？ You wrote the book review？
Ah, did Takane read it with you？
I see... Hmm？ No way, this book review...
Well, good work. I'll read the book review with all my heart. See, a chime.
Huh... I ended up relying on ▲高嶺＊＊▲ until the end.
It's a very good book. I want you to read it to the end. I'm sure you'll love it. Then if,――
If we have a daughter, can you recommend it to her？ It's a book Mama and Papa will love...
Umm... that's in the future, okay？
(I'll try my best to read it until the end！)
Huh, the spelling of the tittle...
